{
  "texts": [
    "This model prediction reflects an effect running from occupational choice to chatbot adoption.",
    "The causality may also run the other way, however, with chatbots prompting workers to move into new occupations.",
    "The theoretical framework abstracts from this occupational-choice margin to keep the analysis tractable.",
    "The frictionless sorting model (Equation (26)) predicts that all adopters sort into encouraged firms, while all non-adopters sort into non-encouraged ones, leaving no workers left to identify Equation (41).",
    "In practice, however, Section 3 finds little evidence of worker resorting in response to chatbot adoption."
  ]
}